HEADWORD: Pierre-perdu
<hw>Pierre`-per`du"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pierre perdue</ets> lost stone.]</ety> <def>Blocks of stone or
concrete heaped loosely in the water to make a foundation (as for a sea
wall), a breakwater, a mole, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piet</ent>⟦br⟧
